779
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:22,000
<i>The Brody twins, Rick and Vic,</i>

780
00:58:22,100 --> 00:58:24,400
<i>who got along fine at sea</i>
<i>but, for some reason,</i>

781
00:58:24,500 --> 00:58:27,500
<i>once they were on dry land</i>
<i>couldn't stand the sight of each other.</i>

782
00:58:27,700 --> 00:58:31,200
You know, one in every
eight boats never returns.

783
00:58:31,300 --> 00:58:33,500
<i>There was John Grimm,</i>
<i>who sure fit his name.</i>

784
00:58:33,600 --> 00:58:35,400
All hands lost at sea.

785
00:58:35,500 --> 00:58:37,700
<i>From Belvedere, South Dakota.</i>

786
00:58:39,100 --> 00:58:42,000
<i>And Pleasant Curtis</i>
<i>from Asheville, Notch.</i>

787
00:58:42,100 --> 00:58:45,200
<i>Never said a word to anyone,</i>
<i>except himself.</i>

788
00:58:47,300 --> 00:58:47,600
I wrote him constantly.

789
00:58:47,600 --> 00:58:50,200
I wrote him constantly.

790
00:58:51,900 --> 00:58:56,900
<i>I told him I had been invited to</i>
<i>audition in New York City</i>

791
00:58:57,500 --> 00:59:00,100
<i>for the School of American Ballet.</i>

792
00:59:00,200 --> 00:59:01,600
Please stay.

793
00:59:01,700 --> 00:59:03,800
Thank you. Thank you.

794
00:59:05,800 --> 00:59:07,100
You can stay.

795
00:59:09,600 --> 00:59:12,700
<i>But I was relegated to the corps.</i>

796
00:59:13,000 --> 00:59:15,400
<i>Another dancing gypsy.</i>

797
00:59:19,700 --> 00:59:21,200
Benjamin!

798
00:59:21,800 --> 00:59:24,300
How is it when you showed up

799
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:28,300
you were no bigger than a bollard
with one foot in the grave,

800
00:59:28,400 --> 00:59:32,600
but now, either I drink a hell
of a lot more than I think I do,

801
00:59:33,900 --> 00:59:35,500
or you sprouted?

802
00:59:36,400 --> 00:59:38,200
What's your secret?

803
00:59:39,600 --> 00:59:41,200
Well, Captain,

804
00:59:43,000 --> 00:59:44,800
you do drink a lot.

805
00:59:49,600 --> 00:59:53,800
<i>We stayed in a small hotel</i>
<i>with a grand name, The Winter Palace.</i>

806
00:59:53,900 --> 00:59:56,700
